org.jetel.util.primitive

Class DuplicateKeyMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jetel.util.primitive.DuplicateKeyMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map
    Deprecated. 
    use MultiValueMap instead

    @Deprecated
public class DuplicateKeyMap
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map
    Wrapper/Decorator around Map object which allows duplicate values stored under the same key.
    Values are stored in ArrayList, modified getters/setters are defined. The memory footprint is higher than normal HashMap/TreeMap since each value/object is wrapped in ArrayList with size at least 1.
    Since:
    15.5.2006

      • values

        public java.util.Collection values()
        Deprecated. 
        This implementation breaks the standard Map.values() contract !!
        Modifications to returned collection does not change values stored in Map. The collection returned is dynamically generated each time this method is called.
        The returned collection contains ALL stored values.
        Specified by:
        values in interface java.util.Map
